						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/Obasanjo-organic-agriculture-development-center-launched-in-Nigeria" title="Obasanjo organic agriculture development center launched in Nigeria" alt="link">Obasanjo organic agriculture development center launched in Nigeria</a></h2>

	
					<p> 
Nigeria is poised to make its entry into the world of organic agriculture with the launch of the Olusegun Obasanjo Center for Organic Research and Development (OOCORD). The Centre will develop research and knowledge exchange on sustainable, organic agricultural systems to address the duel needs of food security and incomes in Africa. Collaboration and information exchange with other institutions is expected to strengthen OOCORD’s functions. Research in organics has been scattered in several universities and agricultural institutions, so this dedicated institution is expected to give the development of organic agriculture in the country an added boost.Source: African Agriculture, 9 May 2007. </p>
							<p><span class="date">18/07/2007</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/Obasanjo-organic-agriculture-development-center-launched-in-Nigeria">Read more...</a>
</div>
